post_cb({"27333940": {"ParentId": "27333887", "CommentCount": "2", "Body": "<p>The standard does not require any particular floating point representation. [basic.fundamental]/8:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_27333887_27333940_0\">The value representation of floating-point types is implementation-defined.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>However, as IEEE 754 is very common, support can be checked via <a href=\"http://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/types/numeric_limits/is_iec559\" rel=\"nofollow\"><code>std::numeric_limits&lt;&gt;::is_iec559</code></a>.</p>\n", "OwnerUserId": "3647361", "PostTypeId": "2", "Id": "27333940", "Score": "3", "CreationDate": "2014-12-06T16:44:57.557", "LastActivityDate": "2014-12-06T16:44:57.557"}, "27333887": {"CommentCount": "0", "ViewCount": "60", "CreationDate": "2014-12-06T16:40:56.120", "LastActivityDate": "2014-12-06T16:44:57.557", "Title": "What floating point implementation details are required by the standard?", "AcceptedAnswerId": "27333940", "PostTypeId": "1", "Id": "27333887", "Score": "0", "Body": "<p>Exactly what floating point implementation details are required by the C++11 standard?</p>\n<p>Is some version of IEEE 754 required by the C++ standard?</p>\n<p>Where is this stated in the C++ standard?</p>\n", "Tags": "<c++><c++11><floating-point><language-lawyer>", "OwnerUserId": "1128289", "AnswerCount": "1"}, "bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_27333887_27333940_0": {"section_id": 7217, "quality": 0.6666666666666666, "length": 4}}, "n3337": {"so_27333887_27333940_0": {"section_id": 6961, "quality": 0.6666666666666666, "length": 4}}, "n4659": {"so_27333887_27333940_0": {"section_id": 8726, "quality": 0.6666666666666666, "length": 4}}}});